{"Title": "Impact of COVID-19 on liver function: results from an internal medicine unit in Northern Italy", "Year": 2020, "Source": "Intern. Emerg. Med.", "Volume": "15", "Issue": 8, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 1399, "PageEnd": 1407, "CitedBy": 2, "DOI": "10.1007/s11739-020-02425-w", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85087796517&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2020, The Author(s).Little is known regarding coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) clinical spectrum in non-Asian populations. We herein describe the impact of COVID-19 on liver function in 100 COVID-19 consecutive patients (median age 70 years, range 25\u201397; 79 males) who were admitted to our internal medicine unit in March 2020. We retrospectively assessed liver function tests, taking into account demographic characteristics and clinical outcome. A patient was considered as having liver injury when alanine aminotransferase (ALT) was > 50 mU/ml, gamma-glutamyl transpeptidase (GGT) > 50 mU/ml, or total bilirubin > 1.1 mg/dl. Spearman correlation coefficient for laboratory data and bivariable analysis for mortality and/or need for intensive care were assessed. A minority of patients (18.6%) were obese, and most patients were non- or moderate-drinkers (88.5%). Liver function tests were altered in 62.4% of patients, and improved during follow-up. None of the seven patients with known chronic liver disease had liver decompensation. Only one patient developed acute liver failure. In patients with altered liver function tests, PaO2/FiO2 < 200 was associated with greater mortality and need for intensive care (HR 2.34, 95% CI 1.07\u20135.11, p = 0.033). To conclude, a high prevalence of altered liver function tests was noticed in Italian patients with COVID-19, and this was associated with worse outcomes when developing severe acute respiratory distress syndrome.", "AuthorKeywords": ["Acute respiratory failure", "Coronavirus", "Hepatitis", "Severe acute respiratory syndrome"], "IndexKeywords": ["Adult", "Aged", "Aged, 80 and over", "Coronavirus Infections", "Female", "Hospitalization", "Humans", "Internal Medicine", "Italy", "Liver", "Liver Failure", "Male", "Middle Aged", "Pandemics", "Patients' Rooms", "Pneumonia, Viral", "Retrospective Studies"], "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 1, "EID": "2-s2.0-85087796517", "SubjectAreas": [["Internal Medicine", "MEDI", "2724"], ["Emergency Medicine", "MEDI", "2711"]], "AuthorData": {"55189363300": {"Name": "Lenti M.V.", "AuthorID": "55189363300", "AffiliationID": "60015197, 60026556", "AffiliationName": "Department of Internal Medicine, San Matteo Hospital Foundation, University of Pavia"}, "57215214015": {"Name": "Borrelli de Andreis F.", "AuthorID": "57215214015", "AffiliationID": "60015197, 60026556", "AffiliationName": "Department of Internal Medicine, San Matteo Hospital Foundation, University of Pavia"}, "57217995293": {"Name": "Pellegrino I.", "AuthorID": "57217995293", "AffiliationID": "60015197, 60026556", "AffiliationName": "Department of Internal Medicine, San Matteo Hospital Foundation, University of Pavia"}, "57220428868": {"Name": "Merli S.", "AuthorID": "57220428868", "AffiliationID": "60015197, 60026556", "AffiliationName": "Department of Internal Medicine, San Matteo Hospital Foundation, University of Pavia"}, "6505992224": {"Name": "Miceli E.", "AuthorID": "6505992224", "AffiliationID": "60015197, 60026556", "AffiliationName": "Department of Internal Medicine, San Matteo Hospital Foundation, University of Pavia"}, "57191164684": {"Name": "Aronico N.", "AuthorID": "57191164684", "AffiliationID": "60015197, 60026556", "AffiliationName": "Department of Internal Medicine, San Matteo Hospital Foundation, University of Pavia"}, "52464304100": {"Name": "Mengoli C.", "AuthorID": "52464304100", "AffiliationID": "60015197, 60026556", "AffiliationName": "Department of Internal Medicine, San Matteo Hospital Foundation, University of Pavia"}, "7005484843